The major cause [of the software crisis] 
is that the machines have become several 
orders of magnitude more powerful! To put 
it quite bluntly: as long as there were no 
machines, programming was no problem at 
all; when we had a few weak computers, 
programming became a mild problem, and now 
we have gigantic computers, programming has 
become an equally gigantic problem. In this 
sense the electronic industry has not solved 
a single problem, it has only created them, 
it has created the problem of using its products.

  -- Edsger W. Dijkstra
